# Microservices with Spring Boot

This project demonstrates the implementation of a microservices architecture using **Spring Boot** and **Docker**. It includes service discovery, API Gateway routing, data persistence, API documentation with OpenAPI, and reactive programming.

> ⚠️ This is a work in progress. Updates are made regularly.

---

## Services Overview

| Service           | Description                                 | Port  |
|-------------------|---------------------------------------------|-------|
| Discovery Service | Eureka server for service registry          | 8761  |
| API Gateway       | Routes requests to microservices            | 8080  |
| Product Service   | Handles product-related operations          | 8081  |
| Order Service     | Manages customer orders                     | 8082  |
| User Service      | Manages users and (future) authentication   | 8083  |

---

## Technologies Used

- Java 17
- Spring Boot
- Spring Cloud (Eureka, Gateway)
- Spring Data JPA
- PostgreSQL
- Docker & Docker Compose
- OpenAPI / Swagger
- Spring WebFlux (Reactive programming)

---

## Running the Project

You can run the full stack with Docker Compose:

```bash
docker-compose up --build
